snippet.title: Best digital cameras
snippet.description: Here's where you find the best of the best, our top digital cameras across the board.

snippet.title: Foursquare
snippet.description: The addition of the Explore recommendation engine makes Foursquare a powerful tool that's gone far beyond its simple checking-in roots.

snippet.title: Android Smartwatch
snippet.description: Guess what? A watch company is out there called Android. And it's decided to make smartwatches, too.

snippet.title: Panasonic TC-L65WT600
snippet.description: An input that's more future-proof than its competitors' fails to make the Panasonic TC-P65WT600 a recommendable 4K TV.

snippet.title: Dirt Devil Dash Upright Vacuum
snippet.description: If you're spending money on something, you want it to work. Sadly, the Dirt Devil Dash Upright Vacuum doesn't perform well enough to make it worth $119, especially when other sub-$200 vacuums outperform it by leaps and bounds.

snippet.title: Beats Music (iOS)
snippet.description: We go hands-on with Beats' new premium music service, designed to appeal to people who want a more automated music listening experience.

snippet.title: GE Cafe Series CFE29TSDSS
snippet.description: Get smart (design) with the GE Cafe Series CFE29TSDSS fridge.

snippet.title: Sony Handycam HDR-CX220
snippet.description: The only thing the Sony Handycam HDR-CX220 seems to have going for it is the low price, but "you get what you pay for" has never rung truer.

snippet.title: Songza for iOS
snippet.description: While you can still get playlists by genre or artist, Songza's unique concept of assembling playlists according to your current activity makes it a great download for music lovers.

snippet.title: Google Search for Android
snippet.description: With voice and text input options and Google Now, the Google Search app is the best way to conduct a search on Android.
